19
00:00:18,314 --> 00:00:19,941
<i>Abandoned!</i>

20
00:00:20,024 --> 00:00:23,986
<i>After an assassination attempt by
his forsaken apprentice, Asajj Ventress,</i>

21
00:00:24,237 --> 00:00:26,447
<i>Count Dooku launches
a brutal counterattack</i>

22
00:00:26,531 --> 00:00:30,493
<i>against the Night sisters,
massacring the entire clan.</i>

23
00:00:30,618 --> 00:00:34,330
<i>Forced into exile, Ventress wanders
far into the Outer Rim,</i>

24
00:00:34,413 --> 00:00:37,291
<i>among the castaways
and vagabonds of the galaxy,</i>

25
00:00:37,375 --> 00:00:40,962
<i>seeking her new life that
was foretold by Mother Talzin.</i>

26
00:01:22,587 --> 00:01:24,338
Prow. Straight up.

27
00:01:35,099 --> 00:01:36,100
Another.

28
00:01:39,353 --> 00:01:40,354
Hey, there.

29
00:01:40,396 --> 00:01:44,317
What's a pretty bald babe like you
doing in a desert like this?

30
00:01:45,234 --> 00:01:46,527
Get lost.

31
00:01:46,861 --> 00:01:49,071
Hey! I'm talkin' to you, lady.

32
00:02:02,418 --> 00:02:04,420
I'm not much of a talker.

33
00:02:18,059 --> 00:02:20,227
Uh, compliments of the lizard in the back.

34
00:02:29,737 --> 00:02:31,405
What do you want?

35
00:02:33,741 --> 00:02:37,078
I'm Bossk and this is Latte Razzi.

36
00:02:37,453 --> 00:02:41,123
-We're bounty hunters, and...
-We have a problem.

37
00:02:41,499 --> 00:02:42,541
Hmm.

38
00:02:42,583 --> 00:02:44,585
What kind of problem?

39
00:02:45,002 --> 00:02:47,755
You just killed one of our team.

40
00:02:50,633 --> 00:02:52,134
Sorry about that.

41
00:02:52,802 --> 00:02:56,347
So where did you get the lightsabers?

42
00:02:57,598 --> 00:02:58,808
Stole them.

43
00:03:00,810 --> 00:03:02,603
Bounty hunter, then?

44
00:03:03,604 --> 00:03:04,647
No.

45
00:03:04,855 --> 00:03:08,275
Ever considered it?
You certainly have the right

46
00:03:09,443 --> 00:03:11,195
Disposition.

47
00:03:11,946 --> 00:03:14,865
Never thought about it. Does it pay well?

48
00:03:15,449 --> 00:03:16,909
Very well.

49
00:03:17,868 --> 00:03:22,206
We have a job to do and you owe us a man.

50
00:03:22,790 --> 00:03:28,963
Join our merry band of bounty hunters,
or we turn you over to the authorities.

51
00:03:32,258 --> 00:03:34,051
What do I have to do?

52
00:03:45,980 --> 00:03:47,815
Hey, Bossk, who's your girlfriend?

53
00:03:48,274 --> 00:03:50,109
Shut up, Dengar.

54
00:03:51,318 --> 00:03:52,611
Hey, boss.

55
00:03:54,488 --> 00:03:57,491
"Boss." This is your boss?

56
00:03:58,075 --> 00:04:01,954
You got a problem with that?
My name's Boba, and this is High singer.

57
00:04:03,497 --> 00:04:05,499
I see you've already met Bossk and Latte.

58
00:04:05,833 --> 00:04:06,959
What's your name?

59
00:04:07,752 --> 00:04:09,503
I don't have a name.

60
00:04:10,421 --> 00:04:11,672
So it's going to be like that, huh?

61
00:04:12,173 --> 00:04:15,676
Look, kid, I don't take orders very well.

62
00:04:15,718 --> 00:04:19,305
Especially from someone of your stature,

63
00:04:19,346 --> 00:04:21,974
and obvious lack of experience.

64
00:04:23,684 --> 00:04:29,899
She killed Oked. So she agreed
to fill in for him on this particular job.

65
00:04:30,524 --> 00:04:32,943
Or, like I said,

66
00:04:33,277 --> 00:04:38,115
we can always find another way
to settle your debt.

67
00:04:41,076 --> 00:04:45,664
That won't be necessary,
I'm a little short of work right now anyway.

68
00:04:47,416 --> 00:04:51,921
She's a little rough around the edges,
but we need six hunters.

69
00:04:52,004 --> 00:04:54,465
Without her, we got no job.

70
00:04:55,299 --> 00:04:57,176
Fine. Let's get going.

71
00:04:59,386 --> 00:05:01,222
Don't we settle first?

72
00:05:02,598 --> 00:05:04,642
What? You don't trust us?

73
00:05:04,725 --> 00:05:08,562
When the job's done, you'll get your cut.
Just like the rest of us.

74
00:05:38,342 --> 00:05:42,221
Welcome. Welcome. I am Major Rigosso.

75
00:05:42,805 --> 00:05:44,306
We are thrilled to have you here.

76
00:05:46,016 --> 00:05:49,103
Please allow me the pleasure
of explaining the mission.

77
00:05:50,145 --> 00:05:54,733
These elevators will take us beneath
the surface of the planet below.

78
00:05:54,900 --> 00:05:59,405
Waiting there is a sub tram
which is carrying very precious cargo.

79
00:05:59,947 --> 00:06:04,994
Your mission is to protect the tram
as it makes its way to the final destination.

80
00:06:05,452 --> 00:06:07,454
And what is this precious cargo?

81
00:06:08,080 --> 00:06:10,374
That's none of your concern.

82
00:06:10,457 --> 00:06:12,793
Just make sure it gets where it's going.

83
00:06:13,210 --> 00:06:15,254
And where exactly is it going?

84
00:06:15,671 --> 00:06:21,427
To my lord, Otua Blank.
He rules over this planet with an iron fist.

85
00:06:21,802 --> 00:06:24,138
If you fail to protect his cargo,

86
00:06:24,221 --> 00:06:28,309
losing your bounty
will be the least of your concerns.

87
00:06:29,143 --> 00:06:30,728
This way, please.

88
00:06:33,522 --> 00:06:35,566
Why do we have to travel by sub tram?

89
00:06:35,649 --> 00:06:38,193
Wouldn't it be easier
just to land at our destination?

90
00:06:38,277 --> 00:06:39,904
You'd think so.

91
00:06:39,987 --> 00:06:43,449
The atmosphere of our planet
is completely pressurized,

92
00:06:43,574 --> 00:06:47,369
leaving all aerial travel impossible.

93
00:06:47,453 --> 00:06:50,331
If we attempted to land
on the planet's surface,

94
00:06:50,372 --> 00:06:53,751
our ship would immediately implode.

95
00:06:53,834 --> 00:06:55,294
Sub tram it is then.

96
00:07:07,431 --> 00:07:10,851
So why hire six expensive
bounty hunters to move cargo?

97
00:07:10,893 --> 00:07:12,978
There's a group of marauders

98
00:07:13,020 --> 00:07:16,607
that would like nothing more
than to hijack my master's cargo.

99
00:07:16,690 --> 00:07:21,362
So far, my men have been
ineffective against them.

100
00:07:31,205 --> 00:07:32,873
They've arrived.

101
00:07:42,007 --> 00:07:46,720
No matter what happens,
do not open this box.

102
00:07:46,887 --> 00:07:49,223
You make the rules, I follow them.

103
00:08:00,401 --> 00:08:04,613
So that's it? That is what we're protecting?

104
00:08:04,905 --> 00:08:07,950
Who cares? As long as we get paid.

105
00:08:15,749 --> 00:08:21,714
My lord, Otua Blank, will meet us
on the other side. Good luck.

106
00:08:34,518 --> 00:08:35,936
After them!

107
00:08:48,615 --> 00:08:51,869
<i>Okay, Boba, the cargo is secure.</i>

108
00:08:51,952 --> 00:08:54,413
<i>Latte, you and High singer stay there.</i>

109
00:08:54,455 --> 00:08:56,373
<i>I'll be in the engine room with Bossk.</i>

110
00:08:56,457 --> 00:08:58,792
<i>I sent the new girl and Dengar to the back.</i>

111
00:09:03,589 --> 00:09:07,843
Hello, darling, looks like we're securing
the back platform together.

112
00:09:07,926 --> 00:09:09,261
Wonderful.

113
00:09:15,684 --> 00:09:18,479
So what do you think is in that box?

114
00:09:19,313 --> 00:09:22,983
Whatever it is,
it better be worth all this effort.

115
00:09:53,639 --> 00:09:56,308
Heads up, people, we got company.

116
00:10:00,312 --> 00:10:02,689
Latte, High singer, get ready!

117
00:10:03,607 --> 00:10:04,942
They're here!

118
00:10:06,777 --> 00:10:08,862
Protect the cargo at all costs.

119
00:10:31,635 --> 00:10:32,886
Goodbye.

120
00:10:51,071 --> 00:10:52,739
Oh, no, you don't.

121
00:11:36,283 --> 00:11:37,576
Poodoo.

122
00:11:42,748 --> 00:11:45,083
I'll check the cargo, stay here.

123
00:12:03,644 --> 00:12:05,854
Oh, hey, boss, you'd better get down.

124
00:12:39,263 --> 00:12:42,557
They're boarding from the rear,
I could use a hand back here!

125
00:12:48,021 --> 00:12:51,692
Hold your position !
Bossk, get to the back and help the rookie!

126
00:12:53,193 --> 00:12:54,569
I'm on it.

127
00:13:30,230 --> 00:13:32,316
Stop him, he's the leader!

128
00:14:16,276 --> 00:14:17,402
You!

129
00:14:18,570 --> 00:14:20,614
I want what's mine!

130
00:14:20,781 --> 00:14:23,367
Over my dead body.

131
00:15:00,654 --> 00:15:01,738
What?

132
00:15:02,447 --> 00:15:04,282
Don't worry, I'll protect you.

133
00:15:08,453 --> 00:15:09,496
Hey!

134
00:15:16,837 --> 00:15:18,255
Pluma, are you okay?

135
00:15:18,839 --> 00:15:21,049
Brother, you came for me!

136
00:15:21,967 --> 00:15:23,468
Of course I did.

137
00:15:27,556 --> 00:15:31,017
Well, well, well, what do we have here?

138
00:15:31,852 --> 00:15:33,270
Stay back!

139
00:15:33,520 --> 00:15:36,815
That little girl
is worth a lot of money to me.

140
00:15:37,441 --> 00:15:39,693
Now step aside!

141
00:16:09,389 --> 00:16:10,390
Stop it!

142
00:16:26,490 --> 00:16:27,699
Krismo!

143
00:16:35,165 --> 00:16:37,584
That girl's crazy! We're protecting her?

144
00:16:37,918 --> 00:16:40,337
Try not to be such a novice.

145
00:16:40,420 --> 00:16:43,423
Open your eyes, she's on their side.

146
00:16:43,548 --> 00:16:47,177
It doesn't matter,
tie them down and let's finish this job.

147
00:16:54,392 --> 00:16:58,605
Is this really necessary?
None of this was my choice.

148
00:16:58,730 --> 00:17:03,777
I never asked to be ripped away
from my home, from my family.

149
00:17:05,195 --> 00:17:07,113
You'll never know what it's like.

150
00:17:12,994 --> 00:17:15,914
I wish I didn't, but I do.

151
00:17:16,581 --> 00:17:20,418
You're just doing this for the money.
It's just another job to you.

152
00:17:20,460 --> 00:17:23,547
You don't even care what's going
to happen to us once it's over.

153
00:17:25,257 --> 00:17:27,634
Hey, rookie! I need you in the back.

154
00:17:29,970 --> 00:17:34,808
You're right, you are just another job
that I couldn't care less about.

155
00:17:35,141 --> 00:17:36,560
Don't move.

156
00:17:45,694 --> 00:17:47,529
We're almost to the drop-off point.

157
00:17:47,612 --> 00:17:50,031
Soon, I'll be delivering
that brat to the warlord

158
00:17:50,115 --> 00:17:53,243
and collecting a handsome bounty
which you will get your share of.

159
00:17:53,326 --> 00:17:56,288
Share of? There's only two of us left.

160
00:17:56,329 --> 00:17:57,872
I get half.

161
00:17:58,164 --> 00:18:01,876
Half? Please. You just got to the game.

162
00:18:04,004 --> 00:18:06,881
Boy, don't test me.

163
00:18:07,632 --> 00:18:11,344
I will be delivering the cargo
and collecting the bounty.

164
00:18:12,095 --> 00:18:14,472
No one of true importance
would lower themselves

165
00:18:14,514 --> 00:18:17,225
to trade with a mere boy.

166
00:18:17,642 --> 00:18:20,395
Boy? You have no idea
who you're talking to.

167
00:18:20,478 --> 00:18:22,522
I have been in charge
of this whole operation...

168
00:18:22,564 --> 00:18:25,317
No, you have no idea

169
00:18:25,358 --> 00:18:28,153
who you are talking to.

170
00:18:54,804 --> 00:18:56,556
Welcome!

171
00:18:56,723 --> 00:18:58,933
Ah ! Finally,

172
00:18:59,559 --> 00:19:01,269
my bride.

173
00:19:01,394 --> 00:19:03,730
Uh, bride?

174
00:19:04,773 --> 00:19:06,066
Uh-uh-uh.

175
00:19:06,399 --> 00:19:08,276
Bounty first.

176
00:19:12,614 --> 00:19:15,825
Your unmarked credits as promised.

177
00:19:25,085 --> 00:19:26,419
Enjoy!

178
00:19:29,339 --> 00:19:31,883
My bride! At last!

179
00:19:34,260 --> 00:19:36,221
Ugh!

180
00:19:58,368 --> 00:20:02,288
You pay my price first then you get the girl.

181
00:20:18,471 --> 00:20:21,391
How do I know you won't take the
credits and then hand us over?

182
00:20:21,975 --> 00:20:23,309
You don't.

183
00:20:30,984 --> 00:20:32,485
Run along now.

184
00:20:38,199 --> 00:20:39,534
Thank you.

185
00:21:07,187 --> 00:21:09,522
You made it? I don't believe it!

186
00:21:10,857 --> 00:21:14,402
Here's the payment,
I already subtracted my share.

187
00:21:17,489 --> 00:21:20,742
Boba's is in there too, make sure he gets it.

188
00:21:21,201 --> 00:21:22,577
Where is he?

189
00:21:23,411 --> 00:21:24,913
He'll turn up.

190
00:21:25,705 --> 00:21:29,250
Well, you certainly turned out to
be quite the member of the team,

191
00:21:29,334 --> 00:21:30,710
didn't you?

192
00:21:31,169 --> 00:21:33,296
I'm not part of any team.

193
00:21:33,505 --> 00:21:36,841
You're too good for us now, is that it?

194
00:21:37,884 --> 00:21:40,929
No. Once I was just like you,

195
00:21:41,304 --> 00:21:43,473
but I'm not that person anymore.

196
00:21:44,182 --> 00:21:46,684
Now, I have a future.

197
00:21:46,708 --> 00:21:51,708
http://hiqve.com/

